com.biorecorder.edflib

Class SignalConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.biorecorder.edflib.SignalConfig

  • public class SignalConfig
extends java.lang.Object
    Class (data-structure) that allows to store information about measuring channels (signals). It has the following fields (and their corresponding getters and setters):
    • signal label
    • transducer type (e.g. AgAgCI electrode)
    • physical dimension(e.g. uV or degree C)
    • physical minimum (e.g. -500 or 34)
    • physical maximum (e.g. 500 or 40)
    • digital minimum (e.g. -2048)
    • digital maximum (e.g. 2047)
    • prefiltering (e.g. HP:0.1Hz LP:75Hz)
    • number of samples in each data record
